data.enText: made of rock; full of rocks

data.chText: 困难的；难以维持的；不稳定的
data.enText: difficult and not certain to continue or to be successful

example: they were having a rough time

tr: causing or characterized by jolts and irregular movements

value.def: A rocky place is covered with rocks or consists of large areas of rock and has nothing growing on it.

example.ex: The paths are often very rocky so strong boots are advisable.
example.tran: 路上通常石头很多，所以最好穿结实耐磨的靴子。

value.def: A rocky situation or relationship is unstable and full of difficulties.

example.ex: They had gone through some rocky times together when Ann was first married...
example.tran: 当安刚结婚时，他们已经一起度过了一些艰难时光。

example.ex: Their relationship had gotten off to a rocky start.
example.tran: 他们的关系在磕磕绊绊中开始了。

value.tran: （局势、关系）不稳定的，不稳固的，困难重重的

trans: 落基山脉诸州(位于美国落基山脉地区的八个州)
